"text":"The ocean’s crying plastic blue,"},{"s":32.08,"e":35.86,"text":"The coral’s pale, the storms break through,"},{"s":35.86,"e":39.46,"text":"And if the waves go silent soon,"},{"s":39.46,"e":43.1,"text":"What lullaby will fill their room?"},{"s":43.46,"e":46.88,"text":"They are not hunger with a grin,"},{"s":46.88,"e":50.34,"text":"They are not fins beneath the skin,"},{"s":50.34,"e":54.12,"text":"They are not jokes for us to sing"},{"s":54.12,"e":57.34,"text":"While we destroy everything."},{"s":58.08,"e":61.42,"text":"Children are more than baby sharks,"},{"s":61.42,"e":65.16,"text":"More than shadows, more than sparks,"},{"s":65.16,"e":68.8,"text":"More than names we toss around"},{"s":68.8,"e":72.34,"text":"While heaven watches from the clouds."},{"s":72.34,"e":75.98,"text":"They are the future, breath, and flame,"},{"s":75.98,"e":79.82,"text":"Every child deserves a name,"},{"s":79.82,"e":83.86,"text":"Not a warning in the dark—"},{"s":83.86,"e":87.22,"text":"Don’t call the children baby sharks."},{"s":87.22,"e":90.24,"text":"The sea was not a trash-can grave,"},{"s":90.24,"e":93.94,"text":"The whale was not a ghost to save,"},{"s":94.06,"e":97.8,"text":"The fish were not just food and foam,"},{"s":97.8,"e":101.56,"text":"The ocean was somebody’s home."},{"s":101.56,"e":104.46,"text":"And children are not born to bite,"},{"s":104.46,"e":108.14,"text":"They’re born to dream, to build, to light,"},{"s":108.44,"e":111.96,"text":"To heal the world we nearly lost,"},{"s":111.96,"e":116.34,"text":"Not pay our debts, not bear our cost."},{"s":116.34,"e":119.86,"text":"So teach them wonder, not the chase,"},{"s":119.86,"e":123.52,"text":"Teach them mercy, teach them grace,"},{"s":123.52,"e":127.36,"text":"Teach them oceans still can live"},{"s":127.36,"e":130.88,"text":"If we grow up and learn to give."},{"s":130.88,"e":134.38,"text":"Children are more than baby sharks,"},{"s":134.38,"e":138.44,"text":"More than shadows, more than sparks,"},{"s":138.44,"e":141.88,"text":"More than names we toss around"},{"s":141.88,"e":145.5,"text":"While heaven watches from the clouds."},{"s":145.5,"e":149.26,"text":"They are the future, breath, and flame,"},{"s":149.26,"e":152.94,"text":"Every child deserves a name,"},{"s":152.94,"e":156.92,"text":"Not a warning in the dark—"},{"s":156.92,"e":161.3,"text":"Don’t call the children baby sharks."},{"s":161.3,"e":164.4,"text":"No more turning innocence"},{"s":164.4,"e":168.02,"text":"Into hunger, teeth, and violence."},{"s":168.02,"e":171.5,"text":"No more laughing while the sea"},{"s":171.5,"e":174.5,"text":"Bleeds beneath our luxury."},{"s":174.5,"e":178.4,"text":"Let them be poets, let them be kings,"},{"s":178.4,"e":181.96,"text":"Let them be healers of broken things,"},{"s":181.96,"e":186,"text":"Let them be more than what we ruined,"},{"s":186,"e":191.98,"text":"Let them be proof that love is human."},{"s":192.86,"e":196.34,"text":"Children are more than baby sharks,"},{"s":196.34,"e":199.38,"text":"More than branding, more than marks,"},{"s":199.5,"e":202.94,"text":"More than echoes, more than fear,"},{"s":202.94,"e":207.46,"text":"They are why we’re still here."},{"s":207.46,"e":210.84,"text":"Clean the water, guard the flame,"},{"s":210.84,"e":214.8,"text":"Call each child by a holy name,"},{"s":214.8,"e":218.8,"text":"Raise them higher than the dark—"},{"s":218.8,"e":223.96,"text":"Don’t call the children baby sharks."}],"duration":226.12,"source":"whisper-aligned","generatedAt":"2026-05-30T01:57:12.487Z","stats":{"whisperWords":368,"polishedWords":364,"matched":355,"matchRate":0.975}}